  "response": "The Samsung Galaxy Core Prime (model SM-G360H) was originally released with Android 4.4 KitKat out of the box. Samsung had announced updates to Android 5.0 Lollipop for this device, and the update was rolled out in various regions starting in late 2015. However, the timing of the update depended on the device's region and carrier.\n\nIf your device hasn't received the update yet, you can manually check for it by going to **Settings > About device > Software update**. If the update is available, you should be able to download and install it from there.\n\nIf the update is no longer available or your device is not receiving it, it could be due to regional restrictions, carrier policies, or the fact that Samsung has ended official support for this device. In such cases, you might consider using custom ROMs, but be cautious as this can void your warranty and carry risks.\n\nFor precise and up-to-date information, you can also contact Samsung support or visit their official website.",
